# Refactoring Walkthrough

The project has been successfully modernized to apply the given backend standard principles. Commenting and messaging functionalities have been completely stripped out, and the authentication has been constrained exclusively to the reliable OAuth 2.0 flow.

## 1. Removed Unused & Brittle Features
- **Deleted Modules**: Removed [write_flow/comment.py](file:///Users/manthan/workspace/linkedin-write-flow/write_flow/comment.py) and [write_flow/messaging.py](file:///Users/manthan/workspace/linkedin-write-flow/write_flow/messaging.py).
- **Removed Dependencies**: Stripped `linkedin-api==2.3.1` (Voyager) and its related auth parsing from [auth.py](file:///Users/manthan/workspace/linkedin-write-flow/write_flow/auth.py).

## 2. SOLID Architecture & Separation of Concerns
We transitioned the codebase into a formalized tiered architecture:
- **Repository Layer ([clients/linkedin_client.py](file:///Users/manthan/workspace/linkedin-write-flow/write_flow/clients/linkedin_client.py))**: Abstracted the raw HTTP requests to LinkedIn's official `v2` API into a clean structural client ([LinkedInClient](file:///Users/manthan/workspace/linkedin-write-flow/write_flow/clients/linkedin_client.py#19-114)).
- **Service Layer ([services/post_service.py](file:///Users/manthan/workspace/linkedin-write-flow/write_flow/services/post_service.py))**: Designed [PostService](file:///Users/manthan/workspace/linkedin-write-flow/write_flow/services/post_service.py#9-159), separating the business logic and payload mappings structurally out of raw API fetching.
- **Controller/Orchestration ([writer.py](file:///Users/manthan/workspace/linkedin-write-flow/write_flow/writer.py))**: Refactored [WriteFlow](file:///Users/manthan/workspace/linkedin-write-flow/write_flow/writer.py#17-69). It strictly acts as an object encapsulator and orchestrator tying Auth, Repository, and Service layers together implicitly without tight coupling.

## 3. Fault Tolerance & Error Handling
- **Resilience**: Installed the `tenacity` library to provide **exponential backoff retries** on network latency (`Timeout`), connectivity failures (`ConnectionError`), and 5xx Server Errors in the [LinkedInClient](file:///Users/manthan/workspace/linkedin-write-flow/write_flow/clients/linkedin_client.py#19-114) layer.
- **Structured Errors**: Replaced raw tracebacks with isolated [LinkedInAPIError](file:///Users/manthan/workspace/linkedin-write-flow/write_flow/clients/linkedin_client.py#14-16) exceptions.

## 4. Validation
- The mock testing suite ([test_auth.py](file:///Users/manthan/workspace/linkedin-write-flow/tests/test_auth.py), [test_post.py](file:///Users/manthan/workspace/linkedin-write-flow/tests/test_post.py), [test_writer.py](file:///Users/manthan/workspace/linkedin-write-flow/tests/test_writer.py)) was entirely rewritten for isolation tests against the new dependency injection structure.
- **Status**: Tested natively with 9/9 tests successfully verified passing (including new 3-step API mocking validation).

## 5. Media Upload Support
- Upgraded [LinkedInClient](file:///Users/manthan/workspace/linkedin-write-flow/write_flow/clients/linkedin_client.py#19-114) with a new generalized [put_binary](file:///Users/manthan/workspace/linkedin-write-flow/write_flow/clients/linkedin_client.py#85-114) method that temporarily strips basic `application/json` constraints, adhering to strict multi-domain binary byte requests natively structured with `tenacity`.
- Designed strict private wrappers [_register_image_upload](file:///Users/manthan/workspace/linkedin-write-flow/write_flow/services/post_service.py#63-82) and [_upload_binary_data](file:///Users/manthan/workspace/linkedin-write-flow/write_flow/services/post_service.py#83-90) inside [PostService](file:///Users/manthan/workspace/linkedin-write-flow/write_flow/services/post_service.py#9-159) that automatically orchestrate the required 3-step asset proxy mechanisms internally.
- Exposed a simplified [publish_image_post](file:///Users/manthan/workspace/linkedin-write-flow/write_flow/services/post_service.py#91-153) capability logically to cleanly orchestrate everything seamlessly via the top [WriteFlow](file:///Users/manthan/workspace/linkedin-write-flow/write_flow/writer.py#17-69) object.

## 6. Installable Distribution Package
- Upgraded the repository root with [setup.py](file:///Users/manthan/workspace/linkedin-write-flow/setup.py) making the entire software available securely across your environments directly via `pip install git+https://...`
